TOKYO (AP) A strong earthquake with a preliminary magnitude of 5.0 rocked northern Japan Friday afternoon, but there were no immediate reports of injuries or damage, officials said. 
The tremor was centered at a depth of about 80 kilometers (50 miles) undersea off the coast of Fukushima Prefecture (state), the Central Meteorological Agency said. 
